  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In the type `HashBuilder` in `trie/hashbuilder.go`, the function `accountLeaf` produces `accountNode`, which in turn contains an object of type `Account`. Currently, the `Incarnation` field of this account object is not set, so it remains 0. It stops working when incarnations are not zero, for example, as a result of this change: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/issues/197.\r\nSuggestion is to assign a bit inside the `fieldSet` to the incarnation field and pass it onto the the `accountLeaf` function. It will be easier to make this change after this one: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/issues/179 , so that we do not need yet another tape for incarnations, but simply pass it as an operand.\r\n",
